casebody.data:
Frieda Vocke McGILL, etc., v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 12, 1936. Arthur E. Cooley, of San Francisco, Cal., Ralph W. Smith, of Los Angeles, Cal., and Llewellyn A. Luce, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Atty. Gen., for respondent.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel, ordered cause remanded to Board of Tax Appeals, with directions to enter an order that the correct estate tax deficiency of petitioner is $6,777.33.
